[quote]
[b]Dot Crosshair:[/b] Universally replaces the default crosshair with a dot.  
[b]EAC:[/b] This mod uses custom code that is not compatible with Easy Anti-Cheat.
[/quote]
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5640][img]https://github.com/rdok/7daystodie_mod_dot_crosshair/blob/main/documentation/showcase.gif?raw=true[/img][/url]

[size=5]Features[/size]
[list]
[*] Replaces the default crosshair with a customizable round dot.
[*] [b]With [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/4017]Gears[/url] & [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/2409/]Quartz[/url][/b]:
[list]
[*] [b]Customize Color, Shape, and Size[/b]: Adjust color, shape (round or square), and size. Customize shadow for square shapes.
[*] [b]Vanilla Crosshair[/b]: Option to use the vanilla crosshair for ranged weapons.
[*] [b]Fallback[/b]: Defaults to a round white dot with 75% transparency if Gears & Quartz are not used.
[/list]
[*] [b]Manual Configuration via [b]ModSettings.xml[/b][/b]:
[list]
[*] Edit [b]ModSettings.xml[/b] if Gears & Quartz cannot be used.
[/list]
[*] [b]Visibility and Integration[/b]:
[list]
[*] Hides the crosshair with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/5601]Immersive Crosshair[/url] when not interacting or using iron sights.
[*] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/7daystodie/mods/3252]Danzo No Crosshair[/url] can be used as an alternative to Immersive Crosshair mod.
[/list]
[*] [b]Game Version[/b]: 1.0. Install with [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/about/vortex/]Vortex[/url].
[/list]
